<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="214" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1117,1286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1117,1142]" pageId="3" pageNumber="214">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[296,441,1117,1142]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Apollonaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="3" pageNumber="214" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[296,441,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="214">Apollonaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is poorly studied and as of this writing has previously only been known from a single species (two known specimens in the 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[587,670,1154,1178]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="3" pageNumber="214">USNM</collectionCode>
) in the tropical Atlantic from 
<quantity box="[1019,1147,1154,1178]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.07" metricValueMax="11.74" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="214" unit="m" value="607.0" valueMax="1174.0" valueMin="40.0">40–1174 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Clark" pageId="3" pageNumber="214" refString="Clark, A. M. &amp; Downey, M. E. (1992) Starfishes of the Atlantic. Chapman and Hall, London, 794 pp." type="book" year="1992">
Clark &amp; Downey 
<number box="[1372,1432,1154,1178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="214" value="1992.0">1992</number>
: 
<number box="[151,197,1190,1214]" pageId="3" pageNumber="214" value="230.0">230</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It displays morphological similarities with 
<taxonomicName box="[698,830,1190,1213]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="3" pageNumber="214" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,830,1190,1213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="214">Ceramaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and to a lesser extent 
<emphasis box="[1079,1201,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="214">
<taxonomicName box="[1079,1180,1189,1214]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Peltaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="3" pageNumber="214" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Peltaster</taxonomicName>
a
</emphasis>
nd 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1407,1189,1214]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Sphaeriodiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="3" pageNumber="214" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1236,1407,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="214">Sphaeriodiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that it displays shallow fasciolar channels, a pentagonal body shape (low R:r), and a general similarity in granule distribution on the abactinal and marginal plates.
</paragraph>
